  DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN

    The XXttCCrreeaatteePPooppuuppSShheellll function ensures that the specified class is a
    subclass of Shell and, rather than using insert_child to attach the widget
    to the parent's children list, attaches the shell to the parent's pop-ups
    list directly.

    A spring-loaded pop-up invoked from a translation table already must exist
    at the time that the translation is invoked, so the translation manager
    can find the shell by name. Pop-ups invoked in other ways can be created
    "on-the-fly" when the pop-up actually is needed. This delayed creation of
    the shell is particularly useful when you pop up an unspecified number of
    pop-ups. You can look to see if an appropriate unused shell (that is, not
    currently popped up) exists and create a new shell if needed.

